cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper deals with physical layer security in wireless networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). It also involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) and system design (cs.SY) aspects. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of pilots for channel estimation, which is a common technique in wireless communication systems (cs.MM).
